results.headline: WHITE BALLOON, THE (MOVIE)
results.summary_short: In a true example of Iranian film making, a 7-year-old girl named Razieh (Aida Mohammadkhani) goes out to buy a fat goldfish for the new year. Little else happens, but Jafar Panahi's film combines the French respect for childhood with the African way of using the simplest of transactions to explore a community. Through short, intense encounters, the girl exhibits independence and Mr. Panahi generates visual interest, though he has enough insight into human nature to create dramatic interest, too. -- Janet Maslin
